          <p className="text-zinc-400 mb-4 leading-relaxed">Content velocity solves the second problem. Publishing more often gives the algorithm more data points to work with, increases your surface area for discovery, and compounds your growth over time. But velocity without structure leads to burnout and declining quality. That is where most creators fail. They either produce beautiful, carefully crafted content too slowly, or they publish at high frequency with content that nobody remembers.</p>
